  <brief_title>Open-label Trial of Imatinib Mesylate in Patients With Unresectable Recurrent Glioblastoma Multiforme Expressing PDGFR (Platelet Derived Growth Factor Receptors)</brief_title>
  <official_title>Open-label Trial of Imatinib Mesylate in Patients With Unresectable Recurrent Glioblastoma Multiforme Expressing PDGFR (Platelet Derived Growth Factor Receptors)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Novartis</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Novartis</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is an open label clinical trial of imatinib mesylate 800 mg po/day in a population of
      patients with unresectable, recurrent glioblastoma multiforme. Patients will be treated for
      up to 12 months
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
